I had a bit more of a chance to play with the spine this weekend, and I am just adding a few observations.<br>
<br>
I had it proc within a few hits of engaging, and so as an experiment I stepped back (I was the only melee person) and yep, it took off blind.  Also, it was interesting to note that it did not follow the &quot;normal fear path&quot;... er, not sure if that made sense, but what I mean is, if I were to fear the same mob (speaking as 49 SK atm), it would always follow a set path more or less; but this blinding effect seems to be more random and the mob seemed to zig-zag around.  Interestingly also, it seemed to ignore my skelly pet entirely and only stop to melee again if I got back into melee range (mob still staggered around even tho pet was whacking on it).<br>
<br>
